    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3907: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-27T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 27, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>235. The Minister for Foreign Affairs states that the Nicaraguan Government today
                    sent the Spanish Chargé d’Affaires ad interim in San Salvador its
                    congratulations on the triumph of the forces of General Franco and of the new
                    Spanish government.</p>
                <p>Under Secretary for Foreign Affairs states this to be along the lines of Estrada
                        doctrine<note n="12" xml:id="d523fn12">Instituto Americano de Derecho y
                        Legislación Comparada, <hi rend="italic">La Doctrina Estrada</hi> (Mexico,
                        1930).</note> and tantamount to recognition.</p>
                <p>Nicaraguan Government states this action taken to show its solidarity with
                    Guatemala and Salvador against Communism. Please see my despatch No. 340.<note
                        n="13" xml:id="d523fn13">Dated November 24, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
